HEADWORD: Holystone
<hw>Ho"ly*stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A stone used by seamen for scrubbing the decks of ships.</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holystone</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Holystone
<hw>Ho"ly*stone`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To scrub
with a holystone, as the deck of a vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

